verbose_text: Acetate and propionate levels were both lower in the VAN group (P = 0.02 and P = 0.03), butyrate was lower in the AMX and VAN groups (both P = 0.01), valerate was lower in the AMX, CTX and VAN groups (P = 0.006, P = 0.009 and P = 0.01) and succinate was higher in the AMX, CTX and VAN groups (P = 0.01, P = 0.03 and P = 0.04) compared to the CON group.
